=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Looking at the mapped reaction:

- **Reactant 1**: A bis(2,4-difluorophenyl)methyl carbocation (CH⁺:20)
- **Reactant 2**: A 4-cyanophenyl-indole (nucleophilic heteroarene)
- **Product**: The carbocation carbon C:20 bonds to C:10 (C3 of indole), the C:11=C:10 double bond becomes single, and N:12 goes from NH to NH⁺ (Wheland/sigma-complex intermediate)

